<h1 id="lab-setting-up-git-for-pip-packages">Lab: Setting up git for pip
packages</h1>
<p>To set up a Git repository for hosting pip packages, you need to
first structure your Python project correctly, use a Git hosting service
(like GitHub, GitLab, or Bitbucket), and then use specific pip install
commands to install the package from the repository.</p>
<h2 id="step-1-prepare-your-python-package">Step 1: Prepare Your Python
Package</h2>
<p>Ensure your project is structured as a Python package, which
typically requires a <code>setup.py</code> or
<code>pyproject.toml</code> file at the root. This file tells pip how to
install the package and its dependencies.</p>
<pre class="plaintext"><code>your_package_name/
├── your_package_name/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   └── module.py
├── setup.py
└── README.md</code></pre>
